      "post_content": "At first one might think this is completely unplayable - I also did.  \n  \nI still think only one part of the additional cost - *either* discarding your hand *or* sacrificing all permanents you control - should have done as well at a mana cost of ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) for a lifeloss of 5, but Wizards possibly made both since you could otherwise bring a Swamp, [Dark Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual) and this on turn one.  \nYet that insanity of additional cost can also be used for your advantage:  \n\\*If you can get your opponent to copy the effect. Currently [Hive Mind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive Mind) seems to be the only card available, although using [Pact](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pact)s with it is more advisable most of the time...  \n\\*Try to protect your cards by exiling them for a period of time, e.g. with [flicker](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=flicker) effects (which return the cards at end of turn) or by using cards with phasing.  \n\\*Use cards which trigger when put into the graveyard like [Flagstones of Trokair](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flagstones of Trokair), and play it as... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost2852\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">At first one might think this is completely unplayable - I also did.<br/><br/>I still think only one part of the additional cost - <i>either</i> discarding your hand <i>or</i> sacrificing all permanents you control - should have done as well at a mana cost of <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> for a lifeloss of 5, but Wizards possibly made both since you could otherwise bring a Swamp, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual\">Dark Ritual</a> and this on turn one.<br/>Yet that insanity of additional cost can also be used for your advantage:<br/>*If you can get your opponent to copy the effect. Currently <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive Mind\">Hive Mind</a> seems to be the only card available, although using <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pact\">Pact</a>s with it is more advisable most of the time...<br/>*Try to protect your cards by exiling them for a period of time, e.g. with <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=flicker\">flicker</a> effects (which return the cards at end of turn) or by using cards with phasing.<br/>*Use cards which trigger when put into the graveyard like <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flagstones of Trokair\">Flagstones of Trokair</a>, and play it as... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 2852)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_S